        <type>double</type>
        <definition>double det_threshold</definition>
        <argsstring>(double pfa)</argsstring>
        <name>det_threshold</name>
        <param>
          <type>double</type>
          <declname>pfa</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Threshold eta for a given false-alarm probability. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Exact closed-form inversion of Pfa = exp(-eta^2/2):</para>
<para>eta = sqrt(-2 * ln(pfa))</para>
<para>The threshold is independent of dwell and SNR; it depends only on the desired Pfa.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>pfa</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Desired false-alarm probability; must be in (0, 1). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Threshold eta &gt; 0.</para>
</simplesect>
Example: det_threshold(1e-6) ~ 5.2565 </para>
        </detaileddescription>
